        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 7:32PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 732 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 17 miles southwest of Grass Range, or 21 miles
southeast of Lewistown, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Grass Range and Forestgrove.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM MDT for
central Montana.</instruction>
